objects.text:
Byte is a great tool for self-expression. What's special about it is how it's displayed on our devices. Instead of being adapted for modern smartphones, like Twitter or Tumblr, it was born there.

That makes all the difference in terms of how we create compelling experiences for our readers/followers. We can agree on that much. So what now?

Well, we need to help byte grow. Otherwise, it will gradually shrink and fizzle out.

Talk about byte with friends and family and post your link on your other social media profiles.

objects.text:
Is this a blogging tool? It's difficult to tell. There are a few clues, though. Entries in the new section are mostly half-finished doodles and name-staking. Not much written content. Not saying much. Not yet, at least.

The medium, however, suits succinct, screen-sized blog entries or other short text forms (byte://poems is a great example).

What if Twitter integrated bytes? Instead of information presented in the form of inscrutable, poorly-sized/marked up images (e.g. OneShot) there would be neat little shareable screens.

And I think @Jack agrees.

objects.text:
Unlike a lot of services today, editing or updating one of your existing Bytes is a meaningful action. If someone has viewed your Byte before, we'll let them know about any updates you've made the next time it shows up in their list. And if they've starred (⭐️) your Byte, we'll send a push notification any time you update to let them know!

Cool, why?

This is an early concept that we have to explore together, but here are a few ideas:

- create a Byte for a party invite and update it with new details as they come
- create a Byte for a daily horoscope or weather forecast
- create a "homepage" Byte that links to your other Bytes

Whatever your heart desires. Make anything from tiny jokes to share among your friends to full-blown miniature websites. 

Every Byte you make gets a unique link that you can share any way you like. Bytes are great inserted into an ongoing chat, or as destinations in themselves. 

It's completely up to you!
